  "text": "The I/O Router interconnect congestion data (Section 4.2.4) provides accurate real-time data that correlates to the write traffic moving from a job on Titan into the PFS. This data provides insight into the locality of nodes and the amount of data being written through them. Using this information, we can identify when highbandwidth or periodic I/O traffic occurs. Operationally, we have used the IORCD data and visualizations to extract I/O patterns, such as N:1 or N:N, from large applications to aid in our procurement when more invasive techniques like Darshan [CITATION_1] were unavailable.",
